(CSS)

h1{
  font-family:"arial";
}

p{
  font-family: monospace;
}


body{
  font-size: 20px;
}

#two{
  font-size: 1.0em;
}

p{
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: bold;
}

h1{
  text-align: center;
}


/*
1em = 16px
 2em = 32px
  - in other words, when putting an id= in html, in the css once you identify the individual id tag (#),
 you can edit an idividual paragraph instead of editing them both at once.
 the text-align can move the text. */
